## Accessibility Considerations

Headers provide semantic structure for screen readers and assistive technologies:

- **Screen readers** use headers to navigate document sections
- **Keyboard users** can jump between headers for faster navigation
- **Search engines** prioritize header text for indexing

<Callout type="info">
Proper heading hierarchy improves both user experience and SEO performance.
</Callout>

## Parameters

<ParameterField name="Level (# count)" type="integer" required>
Number of hash symbols (1-6) determining header size and hierarchy level.
</ParameterField>

<ParameterField name="Text content" type="string" required>
The visible header text. Use clear, descriptive language that summarizes the section content.
</ParameterField>

